Source: http://masteringvmware.com/category/esxi-command-line/

Basic Utils:
------------
ls -- used for listing files nad directories
ls -l -- listing with details
pwd -- current working directory
cd -- change directory
date -- find date and time
df [options] -- for getting disk usage statics
  Options:
    --version  show program's version number and exit
    -h         Human readable
    -m         Megabytes
    -k         Kilobytes

Finding ESXI version and updates:
---------------------------------
vmware -l -- for esxi version
vmware -v -- version details with build no
esxcli software vib list -- check for install vib's

Finding hostname and IP address:
--------------------------------
hostname -- get hostname
hostname -i -- get ipaddress

Monitoring ESXI load:
---------------------
esxtop -- display current running process details

Start and Stop service:
-----------------------
 services.sh {start|stop|restart}
